title: Tropica Rotala rotundifolia
description: A classic stem plant with rounded leaves that turn pink to red under high light. Easy to grow and propagate, making it ideal for beginners and experienced aquascapers alike.

title: Tropica Rotala H'Ra
description: A vibrant red stem plant that develops intense coloration under high light and CO2. Grows quickly and creates stunning contrast in planted aquariums.

title: Tropica Ludwigia repens 'Rubin'
description: Deep red Ludwigia variety that provides bold color in the midground or background. Undemanding and suitable for most aquarium setups.

title: Tropica Hygrophila polysperma
description: One of the most forgiving aquarium plants available. Fast-growing stem plant that thrives in nearly any conditions and helps absorb excess nutrients.

title: Tropica Bacopa caroliniana
description: Sturdy stem plant with thick, rounded leaves. Grows upright and provides excellent structure in the background of planted tanks.

title: Tropica Micranthemum 'Monte Carlo'
description: Popular carpeting plant that forms dense, bright green mats. Easier to grow than Dwarf Baby Tears and achieves a lush carpet with moderate light and CO2.

title: Tropica Hemianthus callitrichoides 'Cuba'
description: The famous Dwarf Baby Tears — the smallest aquarium plant available. Creates an immaculate carpet but demands high light, CO2, and nutrient-rich substrate.

title: Tropica Glossostigma elatinoides
description: A classic Takashi Amano carpeting plant with tiny spoon-shaped leaves. Requires high light and CO2 to stay low and compact.

title: Tropica Anubias barteri var. nana
description: The quintessential epiphyte for aquariums. Attach to driftwood or rocks for best results. Extremely hardy and thrives in low light conditions.

title: Tropica Anubias nana 'Petite'
description: Miniature Anubias variety with tiny leaves, perfect for nano tanks and detail work in aquascapes. Extremely slow growing but virtually indestructible.

title: Dennerle Bucephalandra 'Green Wavy'
description: Sought-after Bucephalandra variety with wavy-edged leaves that shimmer under light. Attach to hardscape and enjoy its slow but rewarding growth.

title: Tropica Microsorum pteropus (Java Fern)
description: A staple aquarium epiphyte known for its leathery, lance-shaped leaves. Attach to rocks or driftwood — do not bury the rhizome in substrate.

title: Tropica Microsorum pteropus 'Trident'
description: An elegant Java Fern variety with narrow, forked leaves that create a feathery appearance. Excellent for midground placement on hardscape.

title: Tropica Bolbitis heudelotii (African Water Fern)
description: A beautiful fern with translucent, deeply lobed leaves. Prefers moderate flow and attaches readily to driftwood. Grows slowly but makes a dramatic statement.

title: Tropica Vesicularia dubyana (Java Moss)
description: The most popular aquarium moss. Attaches to any surface and provides shelter for shrimp and fry. Virtually unkillable in most aquarium conditions.

title: Tropica Vesicularia montagnei (Christmas Moss)
description: Named for its branching pattern that resembles Christmas tree fronds. Creates beautiful texture when attached to driftwood or mesh pads.

title: Tropica Taxiphyllum 'Flame'
description: Unique moss with upward-growing fronds that resemble flickering flames. Distinctive appearance makes it a standout in any aquascape.

title: Tropica Vallisneria spiralis
description: A graceful background plant with long, ribbon-like leaves that sway in the current. Propagates readily through runners and fills in background areas quickly.

title: Tropica Crinum calamistratum
description: A striking bulb plant with long, curly dark green leaves. Makes a dramatic focal point in the background. Very hardy once established.

title: Dennerle Bucephalandra 'Red'
description: A stunning red-hued Bucephalandra variety prized by collectors. New leaves emerge with a reddish tint that darkens with age. Attach to hardscape for best results.

title: Tropica Ludwigia palustris 'Super Red'
description: Intensely red stem plant that maintains its color even under moderate lighting. One of the easiest red plants to grow successfully.

title: Tropica Staurogyne repens
description: Compact, bushy foreground plant that stays low without high light demands. Creates dense green patches and is excellent for transitional areas in aquascapes.

title: Tropica Eleocharis acicularis 'Mini'
description: Dwarf hairgrass that forms a fine-textured carpet reminiscent of a freshly mowed lawn. Spreads through runners with CO2 supplementation.

title: Tropica Cryptocoryne wendtii 'Green'
description: A bulletproof midground plant with wavy green leaves. May experience crypt melt after transplanting but recovers quickly. Thrives in low-tech setups.

title: Tropica Hygrophila pinnatifida
description: Unique plant with deeply lobed leaves and a brownish-red underside. Can be planted in substrate or attached to hardscape. Adds interesting texture to any layout.

title: Tropica Rotala 'Green'
description: A bright green Rotala variety with fine, needle-like leaves. Creates beautiful volume in the background and responds well to trimming.

title: Zebra Nerite Snail
description: Striking black and gold striped nerite snail. One of the most effective algae eaters available. Will not reproduce in freshwater aquariums.

title: Horned Nerite Snail
description: Small nerite species with distinctive horn-like protrusions on its shell. Excellent algae grazer safe for planted tanks. Does not eat live plants.

title: Gold Mystery Snail
description: Bright golden-yellow mystery snail that adds color and personality to any tank. Peaceful scavenger that helps clean up uneaten food and detritus.

title: Blue Ramshorn Snail
description: Beautiful blue-shelled ramshorn snail bred for color. Efficient algae and biofilm grazer. Keep population in check by controlling feeding.

title: Assassin Snail (Clea helena)
description: A carnivorous snail that preys on pest snails. Natural biological control for unwanted snail populations. Attractive striped shell pattern.

title: Red Racer Nerite Snail
description: Vibrant red-orange nerite snail with a smooth, glossy shell. Active algae grazer that works tirelessly on glass, rocks, and plant leaves.

title: Yellow Rabbit Snail (Tylomelania)
description: Elegant elongated snail from Sulawesi with a bright yellow body and spiral shell. Slow-moving and peaceful. Prefers warmer water temperatures.

title: Japanese Trapdoor Snail
description: Hardy, cold-tolerant snail that can live in ponds or aquariums. Peaceful algae and detritus eater with an operculum that seals its shell shut.

title: Twinstar Light 600EA
description: Premium full-spectrum LED light designed for 60cm planted aquariums. Delivers high PAR output with excellent color rendition for lush plant growth and vivid fish colors.

title: Twinstar Light 900EA
description: Top-tier LED for 90cm aquariums with adjustable intensity. Promotes dense carpeting growth and brings out red pigments in demanding stem plants.

title: Fluval Plant 3.0 LED 36"-46"
description: Bluetooth-controllable LED with customizable spectrum and scheduling via the FluvalSmart app. Excellent balance of performance and convenience for planted tanks.

title: UNS Titan RGB LED 60cm
description: High-output RGB LED fixture with full spectrum coverage. Slim profile and premium aluminum construction complement modern rimless aquariums.

title: ADA AQUASKY 602
description: Aqua Design Amano's flagship LED light for 60cm tanks. Delivers pristine white light that showcases the natural beauty of aquascapes. Minimalist hanging design.

title: ADA CO2 Advanced System
description: Complete pressurized CO2 system from Aqua Design Amano including regulator, bubble counter, and diffuser. The gold standard for CO2 injection in planted tanks.

title: UNS Pro CO2 Regulator
description: High-quality dual-gauge CO2 regulator with integrated solenoid valve and precision needle valve. Compatible with standard CGA-320 CO2 cylinders.

title: Aquario Neo CO2 Diffuser Original
description: Premium acrylic CO2 diffuser producing ultra-fine mist for maximum dissolution. Clean, minimal design that disappears in the aquascape.

title: ADA CO2 Drop Checker
description: Glass drop checker for monitoring CO2 levels in real time. Color change indicator solution shows green at optimal 30ppm CO2 concentration.

title: NilocG Thrive Liquid Fertilizer 500ml
description: All-in-one liquid fertilizer containing macro and micro nutrients. Simplified dosing for lush plant growth without multiple bottles. Shrimp safe formula.

title: Seachem Flourish 500ml
description: Comprehensive micronutrient supplement for planted aquariums. Provides essential trace elements, vitamins, and amino acids that plants need to thrive.

title: Seachem Flourish Excel 500ml
description: Liquid carbon supplement that provides bioavailable carbon for plants. Useful as a CO2 alternative in low-tech setups or as a complement to pressurized CO2.

title: ADA Aqua Soil Amazonia Ver.2 9L
description: The industry-standard active substrate for planted aquariums. Lowers pH, provides nutrients, and creates optimal root conditions. Reduced ammonia leaching vs. original formula.

title: UNS Controsoil Black Normal 5L
description: Premium Japanese active substrate that buffers pH and provides nutrients for root-feeding plants. Fine granules create a clean, uniform look.

title: CaribSea Eco-Complete Planted 20lb
description: Minerite-based substrate containing live heterotrophic bacteria. No rinsing required — ready to use straight from the bag. Contains iron, calcium, magnesium, and more.

title: Hikari Micro Wafers 45g
description: Tiny semi-floating wafers designed for small tropical fish. Balanced nutrition with color-enhancing ingredients. Minimizes waste in nano tanks.

title: Hikari Algae Wafers 82g
description: Sinking wafers formulated for algae-eating fish like plecos and otocinclus. Contains spirulina and other plant-based ingredients for optimal nutrition.

title: Hikari Shrimp Cuisine 10g
description: Specialized sinking sticks for freshwater shrimp. Rich in natural color enhancers and essential minerals that support healthy molting and vibrant coloration.

title: ADA Pro Scissors Spring Type
description: Professional-grade stainless steel spring scissors designed for precision trimming of stem plants and carpet plants. Ergonomic spring mechanism reduces hand fatigue.

title: ADA Pro Pinsettes (Straight)
description: Long stainless steel tweezers for precise planting of stem plants and small epiphytes. Essential tool for creating detailed aquascapes without disturbing neighboring plants.

title: UNS Aquascaping Tool Set 5-Piece
description: Complete starter tool kit including straight and curved scissors, straight and curved tweezers, and a substrate spatula. Great value for new aquascapers.

title: Neocaridina Cherry Shrimp - Fire Red
description: High-grade fire red cherry shrimp with solid opaque coloration. Hardy and easy to breed, making them perfect for beginners. Excellent algae grazers.

title: Neocaridina Blue Dream Shrimp
description: Stunning deep blue shrimp with consistent coloration. Same easy care requirements as cherry shrimp but with a striking blue appearance.

title: Amano Shrimp (Caridina multidentata)
description: The legendary algae-eating shrimp popularized by Takashi Amano. Larger than cherry shrimp and voracious hair algae consumers. A planted tank staple.

title: Seachem Matrix 1L
description: Highly porous biomedia with massive surface area for beneficial bacteria colonization. Supports both aerobic and anaerobic filtration for complete nitrogen cycle processing.

title: Seachem Purigen 250ml
description: Premium synthetic adsorbent that polishes water to crystal clarity. Removes nitrogenous organic waste, tannins, and phenols. Rechargeable with bleach.

title: Catappa Indian Almond Leaves 10-Pack
description: Natural Indian almond leaves that release beneficial tannins, lower pH, and provide biofilm for shrimp grazing. Essential for blackwater setups and shrimp tanks.

title: Alder Cones 25-Pack
description: Tiny pine cone-like botanicals that release gentle tannins and provide grazing surfaces for shrimp. A staple supplement for any shrimp keeper.

title: Seiryu Stone 10lb Box
description: Classic aquascaping stone with dramatic grey and white veined patterns. Creates stunning iwagumi layouts. May raise pH and hardness slightly.

title: Dragon Stone (Ohko) 10lb Box
description: Highly textured stone with pitted, cave-like surfaces. Lightweight and inert — does not affect water chemistry. Ideal for natural-looking hardscape layouts.

title: Landen Spiderwood Medium
description: Intricate branching driftwood with a spider-web-like structure. Creates dramatic centerpieces and provides attachment points for epiphytes and mosses.

title: Manzanita Driftwood Large
description: Elegant driftwood with smooth, twisted branches. Sinks quickly and leaches minimal tannins. Perfect for creating natural tree-like structures in aquascapes.

title: Seachem Prime 500ml
description: The most concentrated dechlorinator on the market. Detoxifies chlorine, chloramine, ammonia, nitrite, and nitrate. Essential for every water change.

title: Seachem Stability 500ml
description: Beneficial bacteria supplement for rapidly cycling new aquariums. Contains synergistic blend of aerobic, anaerobic, and facultative bacteria strains.

title: API Freshwater Master Test Kit
description: Comprehensive liquid test kit covering pH, High Range pH, Ammonia, Nitrite, and Nitrate. Over 800 tests per kit. Far more accurate than test strips.

title: API GH & KH Test Kit
description: Liquid test kit for measuring General Hardness and Carbonate Hardness. Critical for monitoring water parameters in shrimp tanks and planted aquariums.

title: Marina Naturals Rock Outcrop Large
description: Realistic resin rock decoration that provides hiding spots for fish. Non-toxic and safe for all freshwater aquariums. Easy to clean and maintain.

title: Fluval E100 Electronic Heater 100W
description: Advanced electronic heater with LCD temperature display and dual temperature sensors for precise control. VueTech technology shows real-time water temperature.

title: Oase HeatUp 100W
description: Sleek, compact aquarium heater with precise thermostat control. Shatterproof design and auto shut-off safety feature. Blends seamlessly in planted tanks.

title: USB Nano Air Pump Ultra Quiet
description: Whisper-quiet USB-powered air pump perfect for nano tanks up to 10 gallons. Adjustable airflow and virtually silent operation. Great for sponge filters.

title: Fluval Fine Mesh Fish Net 6"
description: Soft fine-mesh net that is gentle on fish fins and scales. Long ergonomic handle provides easy reach into deep tanks without stressing fish.

title: Marina Breeding Box Large
description: Floating breeding box for isolating pregnant livebearers, injured fish, or aggressive tankmates. Transparent design with adjustable divider and air-driven water circulation.

title: Aquarium Background Black 24"x48"
description: Solid black vinyl background that creates depth and makes fish and plant colors pop. Easy to apply with tape or static cling. Trimmable to fit any tank.

title: Brightwell Aquatics Remineraliz-P 250g
description: Premium remineralizer specifically formulated for planted shrimp tanks. Restores essential minerals to RO/DI water with precise GH and TDS targeting.

title: Dennerle Nano Corner Filter
description: Ultra-compact internal corner filter designed for nano aquariums up to 10 gallons. Silent operation with adjustable flow. Includes biological and mechanical media.

title: NilocG Thrive Caps Root Tabs 30-Pack
description: Concentrated root fertilizer tabs that deliver nutrients directly to plant roots. Long-lasting formula with macro and micronutrients. Essential for heavy root feeders like swords and crypts.
